Delete a Row-Level Formula

When you no longer need a row-level formula in your report, delete it.

To create, edit, and delete formulas in private reports:
Enhanced Folder Sharing

To create, edit, and delete formulas in public and private reports:
Enhanced Folder Sharing

Report Builder OR Report Builder (Lightning Experience)

Delete row-level formulas directly from the Lightning report builder. 
Edit a report.
From the Columns section of the Outline pane, find the row-level formula you want to delete and click x.
If you mistakenly remove a row-level formula from the report, you can recover it by clicking .
To save and run the report, click Save & Run.

The row-level formula column is removed from the report and from the row-level formulas folder in the Fields pane.
title: Deleting Row-Level Formulas
